label: High blood pressure or hypertension (except that occurred during pregnancy and did not last after pregnancy)?
Diabetes? Do not include pre-diabetes.

"Coronary artery disease (blockages in your heart vessels) or angina (chest pain)?

CAD is when plaque buildup (atherosclerosis) in your coronary arteries (the blood vessels of the heart) that leads to clogs. The arteries narrow, limiting blood flow to the heart. This can lead to a heart attack or angina (chest pain).

"

"A heart attack (myocardial infarction)?

A heart attack(AKA myocardial infarction or MI) is the death of heart muscle from the sudden blockage of a coronary artery (blood vessel of the heart) by a blood clot. This injury can cause chest pain or pressure.

"

"Congestive Heart failure (CHF, Heart Failure)?

Heart Failure is heart pumping that is weaker than normal. It does not mean the heart has stopped working. This can cause fluid build-up in the legs, lungs, or other organs (edema).

"

"Stroke or TIA (Transient Ischemic Attack or Mini-Stroke)?

A stroke is the disruption of blood supply to part of the brain due to either narrowing of the blood vessels in the brain (plaque buildup), a blood clot to the brain, or a brain hemorrhage (internal bleeding). This can cause a variety of neurologic symptoms. When the symptoms resolve completely within 24 hours, it is called a TIA (transient ischemic attack).

"

"Atrial fibrillation (Afib, AF)?

AF is an irregular heartbeat (arrhythmia) that can lead to blood clots, stroke, heart failure and other heart-related complications. Some people refer to AF as a quivering heart.

"
